# Lattice Physics — AT API Reference

## Loading
- `ring = at.load_m('file.m')` — Load MATLAB lattice
- `ring = at.load_lattice('file.mat')` — Load MAT-file
- `len(ring)` — Element count
- `ring.energy` — Beam energy [eV]
- `ring.get_s_pos(range(len(ring)+1))` — s positions

## Linear Optics
- `ld0, rd, ld = at.get_optics(ring, refpts=range(len(ring)+1), get_chrom=True)`
  - `ld.beta` — Beta functions (Nx2 array: beta_x, beta_y)
  - `ld.dispersion` — Dispersion (Nx4 array: eta_x, eta_px, eta_y, eta_py)
  - `rd.tune` — Tunes [nu_x, nu_y] (fractional, same as `at.get_tune`)
  - `rd.chromaticity` — Chromaticities [xi_x, xi_y]
- `at.get_tune(ring)` — Fractional tunes only (integer parts not included)
- `at.get_chrom(ring)` — Chromaticities [xi_x, xi_y]

### ALS Working Point
- nu_x ≈ 14.25, nu_y ≈ 8.18 (integer parts: 14, 8)
- `at.get_tune()` and `rd.tune` return fractional parts only (~0.25, ~0.18)

## Fitting
- `at.fit_tune(ring, 'QF', 'QD', [nux, nuy])` — Fit tunes (in-place)
- `at.fit_chrom(ring, 'SFF', 'SDD', [xi_x, xi_y])` — Fit chromaticities (in-place)

## Tracking
- `ring.track(rin, nturns=N)` — Track 6D phase-space vector for N turns
- `ring.track(rin, nturns=N, refpts=[0])` — Get turn-by-turn data at observation point
- Input: rin shape (6,) or (6, nparticles); output includes NaN if particle lost
- Survival check: `np.all(np.isfinite(rout))` — True if particle survived all turns

## Element Access
- `[e for e in ring if e.FamName == 'QF']` — Find by family
- `ring.get_uint32_index(at.Quadrupole)` — Indices of all quadrupoles
- `elem.K` — Quadrupole strength
- `elem.H` — Sextupole strength
- `elem.Length`, `elem.BendingAngle`, `elem.PassMethod`

## Visualization
Use `save_artifact(fig, "title")` to register plots in the artifact gallery.
Works in both `execute` and sandbox tools (`create_interactive_plot`, etc.) —
all support `at` imports.
